    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-01-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-01-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="294" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Young</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-01-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 31,
                                1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No: 76.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose herewith for your information
                            copy of a letter from the president of the Pacific Mail Steamship
                            Company, and copy of the Department’s reply thereto, in relation to the
                            firing upon the steamer <hi rend="italic">Costa Rica</hi> in the port of
                            Amapala, Honduras, and the position of commanders of merchant vessels as
                            regards demands for the surrender of criminals.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
